  • Package structures

    • Class structures.MatchResult extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • redTeam

          java.util.ArrayList<E> redTeam
          An array list containing the members of the red team.

        • blueTeam

          java.util.ArrayList<E> blueTeam
          An array list containing the members of the blue team.

        • date

          java.lang.String date
          The date when the match was conducted.

        • odds

          double odds
          The odds of of red team winning the match (ex 0.57).

        • winner

          WinningTeam winner
          True if red team won the match.

          MatchResultStatusEnum recordStatus

    • Class structures.Player extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • id

          java.lang.String id
          id is a unique player identifier created by discord. It is typically a large string of numbers. It could be represented by a numeric format, but is formatted as a string to prevent the number from potentially overflowing.

        • name

          java.lang.String name
          name is a non-unique player name used by discord. This is the display name user's see in the discord server (guild)

        • u

          int u
          u is the mean of the normal distribution of a player's rating. This can be considered the ELO or MMR of the player.

        • sigma

          int sigma
          sigma is the variance of the player's rating. Currently, sigma does not change from game to game.
